race.comment: ZIPPING ZEYATTA (1) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 520m at this track two runs back then raced on speed again when finishing third at this track last start. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Makes plenty of appeal. NEW SURPRISE (7) could manage only fifth at this track last time but impressed when clocking a quick 22.84 over 401m at this track the start prior. Expected to feature on best figures. TAP OUT BEAU (6) trailed the lead and fought on well to be beaten 2 lengths into second (22.88) at this track in a Grade 5 over 401m. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Expected to be in this for a long way. EXTRAORDINAIRE (5) jumps at a shorter journey and still warrants respect.
